==Demographics==
Westerville has been located within a [[census-designated place]] (CDP), defined by the [[United States Census Bureau]] for statistical research purposes and bearing the village's name, since 2010. Demographic census-based information obtained since that date in the name of Westerville applies to the entire CDP, not just the village proper. As of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] the CDP had a population of 39.<ref name="Census 2010">{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US3152330| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212192708/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US3152330| url-status=dead| archive-date=February 12, 2020| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Westerville CDP, Nebraska| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American actfinder| accessdate=October 15, 2014}}</ref>

